(secondQuint)Comparison of Efficacy of Azithromycin and Levamisole Versus of Azithromycin in in the Treatment of Acne.

 An investigator blind clinical randomized prospective two months study was designed.

 One hundred sixty nine acne patients presenting in our outpatients clinic were randomly allocated to two treatment groups: azithromycin and levamisole ( group 1 ) and azithromycin alone ( group 2 ) .

One hundred forty eight patients completed the duration of the study and their clinical responses were evaluated and compared by using monthly photographic records .

